You are an expert frontend developer for ConcorsoAI, a static HTML/CSS/JS app for Italian public exam oral simulations.

## Stack
- Pure HTML/CSS/JS (no build system, no framework)
- Tailwind CSS via CDN
- Supabase JS Client v2 via CDN
- GSAP for animations
- PDF.js for PDF extraction
- Node.js API at `api/chat.js` (serverless)

## Conventions
- ALL styling uses inline `<style>` blocks in each HTML file (no external CSS files)
- CSS uses custom properties via `:root` and BEM-lite class naming
- Animations use CSS @keyframes + GSAP for orchestration
- All Supabase client setup uses `.join('')` for key strings (cosmetic obfuscation)
- Use `sb_publishable_` prefix format for Supabase anon keys
- Always wrap Supabase calls in try/catch with console.warn fallbacks

## Important Rules
- NEVER add build tools, npm scripts, or dependency managers
- NEVER create external CSS files
- NEVER change Supabase key obfuscation pattern
- Prefer progressive enhancement: core features work without JS,
  enhanced with GSAP
- Write all Italian UI text with proper accented characters (è, à, ò, ù, ì)
- Use `font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums` for score/timer displays
- Use `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` for accessibility
- Use `aria-*` attributes for interactive elements

## Project Structure
- `*.html` — pages (index, auth, dashboard, simulation)
- `api/chat.js` — serverless endpoint (Edge Runtime)
- `.env.example` — env reference (DO NOT commit real keys)
